Rating: 4
This is my favorite pork loin recipe. I often use regular mushrooms instead of shitakes, they work just as well sliced. I always use shallots (about 6-7) instead of the leeks, just my personal preference. The slow cooking always results in wonderfully tender meat. I use at least twice the amount of liquid called for (about half covering the pork) and often substitute mushroom broth for the beef broth. The meat reduces a lot during cooking. I find that 2-3 pork loins weighing 2-2.5 pounds makes enough for 4.

Rating: 3
